RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 1 220 Y Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ST PADDY 109 away well, dug in late to get by. FIRED caught late. EYE M broke outward into NOT EASY BEING ME and closed late. MISS FANCY NANCY drifted in midstretch and rallied late. YUMAS FIRST DASH broke inward into NORTHFORK THREE TEN and was outkicked under urging. NOT EASY BEING ME sandwiched away from the gate. NORTHFORK THREE TEN sandwiched leaving. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race. After review EYE M was disqualified and placed sixth for interference to NOT EASY BEING ME and NORTHFORK THREE TEN. YUMAS FIRST DASH was disqualified and placed seventh for interference to NOT EASY BEING ME and NORTHFORK THREE TEN.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $5,000 .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RYANWATER raced from the back of the pack, took closer order in the far turn, drove five wide into the lane, then continued a four-wide bid and drew clear in the final sixteenth to prove best, driving. FULL VELOCITY went three to four wide into the opening turn, contested the lead leaving the backstretch, drew clear in the final turn, was overtaken midstretch and finished second best. FROBISHER BAY sat in striking position from along the rail, chased four wide into the lane, but was no match in the drive. TALKIN MALICE hurried outside angling in, in the first turn, attended the pace from the three path, was unable to keep pace with rivals and gave way. FLASH OF GLORY offered little. VISION QUEST was quickest leaving the opening turn, was overtaken and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Vision Quest
ENTRY.OWNER: Kleparchuk Victor Kleparchuk Mike and Viking Stables

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 91. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $2 2,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANCING WILLIE was reserved off the early pacesetters, advanced quickly through the final turn outside, set sights on GODGUNSNCOUNTRY at the head of the stretch, and won driving. TACOFLAVOREDKISSES trailed early, was roused near the quarter pole, closed gradually from the four path, and was along in time for place honours. MACHINE went four to five wide into the early turn, closed steadily under light handling and got by just in time to score show. GODGUNSNCOUNTRY lead the way early, drew away nearing the quarter pole, yielded in the stretch and was caught late. EXPLODE sat just off the pace from the three path, and faded. THE BEAT was outrun throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Spangled Jimmy H. CENTURY MILE RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 96. Stakes Purse 50000. A BLACK TYPE HANDICAP STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD. A fee of $100.00 required to nominate. A payment of $500.00 is required to pass the entry box and an additional $400.00 is required to start. The purse will be divided $30,000 to the owner of the winner, $10,000 to the second place finisher, $5,000 to the third place finisher, $2,500 to the fourth place finisher and $1,000 to the fifth place finisher. A payment of $500.00 will be paid to all horses who start and finish sixth or worse. High weight s preferred. Starters to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The field will be limited to 12 starters. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREEK GEEK sat in striking distance while wide through the backstretch, went four wide through the far turn then started to quicken, drove five wide at the head of the lane, rallied determinedly outside, dug in and prevailed after a multi-horse scramble to the wire. MASKWECIS rated off the early pace, rallied four wide at the head of the lane, kept under handling from between foes and was out finished in the final yards. DRINKING AGAIN chased through the far turn from a rail position, angled out to the three path, fought on gamely inside of MASKWECIS and GREEK GEEK, and yielded grudgingly. GLAVA contested the early pace outside of ASYOUBELIEVE, gained a short advantage entering the final turn, and got caught. COUNTRIFIED trailed the field early, and bid belatedly. ASYOUBELIEVE contended the early pace inside of GLAVA, was unable to match strides entering the stretch and wilted. SLAATS stalked the pacesetters from the rail and lacked a bid.

ENTRY.OWNER: Shot In The Dark Racing Corp.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, angled 3w, gamely inside, yielded grudgingly

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHURAZ vied outside for the early lead, contended the pace through the backstretch while four to five-wide, dueled outside of LIFES ADVENTURE entering the stretch, dug in and edged clear. DADDY'S PEPPER stalked the pacesetters outside, hustled on the final turn then finished willingly in the late stages and got up for second. LIFES ADVENTURE pressed the pace from along the rail, responded to a challenge from SHURAZ, and was rundown. BARAK attended the pace between rivals, and lacked a closing response. AL REICHERT lagged early while wide, and improved late. HANDSOME HENRY failed to threaten. BIG JIM chased outside and faded. PACHECO showed little.

ENTRY.NAME: Shuraz
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 4-5w, dug in, edged clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000 (Lesser Claiming Races For $3, 500 (AB $4,500) At Century Mile Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DANZA UNBRIDLED bumped away from the gate, chased through the final turn, rallied four wide into the stretch, dug in between foes, and prevailed under a long drive. VICTORY AT LAST tracked wide leaving the backstretch, rallied steadily outside of DANZA UNBRIDLED, and was bested in the final yards. INDEPENDENCE NEIGH brushed leaving, chased the leader, drifted out under left-handed encouragement, and weakened deep stretch. J. CRUZ jostled away, showed the way through the backstretch, was under attached approaching the stretch, and came up empty in the drive. HIGH KELLY SONG bumped from the gate, sent for speed early, and improved position late. PUMP THE BRAKES bumped repeatedly leaving, rated off the early pace, and lacked a kick. SNAP COUNT was not a factor. IMPERIAL BIRD sandwiched leaving the gate, raced wide leaving the backstretch, fell nearing the quarter, did not finish, and was vanned off. MAJOR SHEPARD chased outside, fell over a fallen horse losing his rider, did not finish and walked off. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of J.CRUZ against the rider of INDEPENDENCE NEIGH alleging interference in the stretch was not allowed. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the final turn of the race but made no change. *POST TIME was delayed due to an injured jockey.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M DASHING stalked five wide, drew closer nearing the stretch, and prevailed under a drive. DUNE D'ORO dropped back leaving the backstretch, and bid belatedly improving position from along the rail. UPO lagged early and offered a late bid. JULIUS THE GREAT vied inside for the early lead, dueled in the final turn, was unable to move on with rival and gave way.
